---
import Layout from '@/layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About Apologify — Say sorry in a way that lands"
  description="Why we built Apologify: turning a hard “I'm sorry” into a page that actually gets opened, read, and kept."
>
  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <span class="inline-block text-sm font-semibold tracking-widest uppercase text-primary font-sans">About</span>
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-base-content mt-3 mb-6" style="text-wrap: balance;">
      We help you say sorry in a way that lands
    </h1>

    <div class="space-y-5 text-lg text-base-content/80 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Apologizing is hard — and when it finally matters, the usual options let you down.
        A plain text gets buried and read as low effort. A copied template sounds fake.
        A wall of AI text has nowhere to live.
      </p>
      <p>
        Apologify turns a written apology into something worth giving: we help you find sincere,
        personal words, wrap them in a design you choose, and hand you a link — a real page the
        other person can open, read, and keep.
      </p>
      <p>
        It's built for the moments that actually happen: the partner you let down, the friend you
        forgot, the parent you owe a call, the customer who deserves a straight answer. Not a
        greeting card, not a form letter — <em>your</em> apology, made to be received.
      </p>
      <p>
        Creating and sharing your page is free, with no account needed to start. Because the goal
        was never to sell you something — it's to help you make things right.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10">
      <a href="/generator" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Make your apology page</a>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>
